Before starting any task in this project, read @_docs/SKILL.md for the step-by-step workflow.

Then read in order:
- @_docs/start-here.md — golden rules and entry point
- @_docs/structure/project-rules.md — naming and file conventions
- @_docs/learnings.md — common mistakes (read the top 10 before writing any code)

Key rules enforced in this project:
- Never use a bare `<img>` — always `<Image>` from `next/image`
- Never use `<figure>` unless a `<figcaption>` is present (`next/image` handles `<picture>` internally)
- Use `<Link>` from `next/link` only for internal Next.js routes; use plain `<a>` for `mailto:`, `tel:`, and external URLs
- No CSS modules — use Tailwind utilities or PostCSS under `src/assets/css/`
- All components are props-driven — no hardcoded content, no internal data fetching
- All values in rem, never px
- Every new component needs a preview page at `src/app/components/<name>/page.tsx`

For Figma extraction tasks, also read the relevant contract under `_docs/front-end/`.
